# =============================================================================
# sap-dev .gitattributes
#
# Purpose: freeze the byte content of the data files that the offline
# regression suite (sap-dev/tests/fixtures/) and the shared reference tables
# depend on, so a checkout on a Windows CI runner cannot silently rewrite
# them.
#
# Why this matters (documented failure modes in this repo):
#   * TSV files carry REAL TAB bytes as field separators. A line-ending or
#     whitespace filter that touches them corrupts the schema silently — and
#     a corrupted TSV "reads fine" until a column shifts. (Hit twice: SE11
#     .def files, the sap-migrate knowledge-pack TSVs.)
#   * Golden .abap outputs and frozen work-folder extraction files are
#     compared / schema-checked byte-for-byte by the regression harness. If
#     actions/checkout normalises CRLF<->LF differently than the author's
#     working copy, fixture-integrity checks pass locally and fail in CI
#     (or, worse, pass against corrupted bytes).
#
# `-text` tells git to treat the path as binary for end-of-line purposes:
# never apply CRLF<->LF conversion, never run a text filter. The exact bytes
# that were committed are the exact bytes that are checked out, on every OS.
# =============================================================================

# Reference tables (shared/tables/*.tsv) and any fixture TSV: real TABs, frozen.
*.tsv          -text

# ABAP source: the shipped sample, fixture goldens, and any committed .abap.
*.abap         -text

# Everything under the regression fixtures is frozen byte-for-byte: specs,
# frozen extraction (_*.txt), committed RFC signature snapshots, goldens,
# and the per-case expectation JSON. -text on the whole tree is the simplest
# guarantee that fixture-integrity / golden checks see identical bytes in CI.
tests/fixtures/**   -text

# Design-spec workbooks and other binary assets: mark binary so git never
# attempts a text diff or eol conversion on them.
*.xlsx         binary
*.xlsm         binary
*.pdf          binary
*.png          binary
*.bmp          binary
